<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-23T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-23T03:00:00-05:00" n="738" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d738">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2649: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Warren</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-23T17:00:00+09:00"><hi rend="italic">August 23,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 23—8:06
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>140. Your number 87, August 11, 5 p.m., received August 15th and your
                            number 91, August 15, 5 p.m., under date of August 16. I formally
                            communicated memorandum to Foreign Office and asked for reply and today
                            I am in receipt of reply under date of August 22nd in exact terms of
                            memorandum transmitted in my number 135, August 9, 1 p.m. I am sending a
                            copy of my note and reply by mail.<note n="80" xml:id="d738fn80">Neither
                                printed.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>